+# PR-214 Remediation Report
+
+## Thread Triage
+
+- Actionable: `T-214-01`, `T-214-04`, `T-214-05`
+- Duplicate: `T-214-02`
+- Obsolete: `T-214-03`
+
+## Code and Docs Changes
+
+- `src/policy/approval_router.py`: Normalize approval state before building the preview payload so fallback responses do not leak `manual_review`.
+- `src/policy/preview.py`: Keep `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` in the `preview_unavailable` payload.
+- `tests/test_preview.py`: Added a regression covering `preview_enabled=False` with `manual_review` input.
+- `docs/approval_policy.md`: Corrected the fallback payload example and notes.
+
+## Verification
+
+- Target behavior now preserves `approval_state="human_review_required"` and `requires_human_review=true` when `build_policy_preview(..., preview_enabled=False, approval_state="manual_review", ...)` is called.
+- Intended test run: `python3 -m unittest tests/test_preview.py tests/test_approval_router.py`
